---

🔥 Step 1: Verify CSV

oc get csv -n openshift-storage | grep rook

👉 If NOT present → that's the issue


---

🔥 Step 2: Force reinstall rook-ceph operator

oc delete subscription rook-ceph-operator -n openshift-storage

Then recreate:

cat <<EOF | oc apply -f -
apiVersion: operators.coreos.com/v1alpha1
kind: Subscription
metadata:
  name: rook-ceph-operator
  namespace: openshift-storage
spec:
  channel: stable-4.19
  name: rook-ceph-operator
  source: cs-redhat-operator-index-v4-19
  sourceNamespace: openshift-marketplace
  installPlanApproval: Automatic
EOF


---

🔄 Step 3: Watch operator come back

watch oc get csv -n openshift-storage

👉 You should see:

rook-ceph-operator.v4.19.x → Installing → Succeeded


